@host = http://localhost:5030
@token = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### Auth — obtain JWT (required for all other endpoints)
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "owner",
  "password": "12345678"
}

### Refresh access token
POST {{host}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{login.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### Warehouses ----------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/api/warehouses
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Reactivate a warehouse
PATCH {{host}}/api/warehouses/{{warehouseId}}/reactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Products — browse catalog -------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/api/products?page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Search (FTS5 + filters, including sectionId)
GET {{host}}/api/products/search?query=rose&sectionId=&page=1&pageSize=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expiring within 30 days
GET {{host}}/api/products/expiring?withinDays=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Image search
# POST {{host}}/api/products/search-by-image?maxResults=10&maxHammingDistance=12
# Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
# Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary
#
# ------boundary
# Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="query.jpg"
# Content-Type: image/jpeg
#
# < ./query.jpg
# ------boundary--

### Alerts --------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/api/alerts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Real-time alerts (SignalR) — connect to /hubs/alerts with access_token query or Bearer
